  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1051167557" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1051167557" />
    <a title="Quentin Wallace" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/33274222-quentin-wallace"><img alt="Quentin Wallace" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1625093327p2/33274222.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1051167557?book_show_action=true">Sep 10, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Quentin Wallace" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Quentin Wallace" href="/user/show/33274222-quentin-wallace">Quentin Wallace</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780812521375" href="/book/show/1063376.Necroscope">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1051167557" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4095275692768391766">This one was..complicated. I finally got around to reading it after putting it off for a while, and I did enjoy it. However, it wasn&apos;t really what I expected and it did have its flaws.<br/><br/>First off, I think it&apos;s a little too lengthy. 100-200 pages could have been cut and it would have been a stronger, tighter story. The story is set during the Cold War, and we see Britain and Russia both utilizing ESP agents, as in agents with some type of mental power. Our two main characters are a necromancer, who</span>
  <span id="freeText4095275692768391766" style="display:none">This one was..complicated. I finally got around to reading it after putting it off for a while, and I did enjoy it. However, it wasn't really what I expected and it did have its flaws.<br /><br />First off, I think it's a little too lengthy. 100-200 pages could have been cut and it would have been a stronger, tighter story. The story is set during the Cold War, and we see Britain and Russia both utilizing ESP agents, as in agents with some type of mental power. Our two main characters are a necromancer, who can speak to the dead only by fondling their organs, and a necroscope, who can converse with the dead (and even control them as we find out later.) The necromancer is evil, but the necroscope is not. Then we end up with a vampire thrown in the mix. Lumley's vampires have most of the same powers and weaknesses as traditional vampires, but <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[ they are an actual, parasitic creature that exists in the human body. Once they are "infected", I mean.  <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span> Things get a little far out by the end, as it turns more into a superhero battling a supervillain rather than a necroscope battling a vampire. <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[ I thought it was a bit much the necroscope could suddenly travel through time and space. Didn't seem to fit the story well to me.  <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br /><br />Overall, I did enjoy it. It was plodding in some parts, nearing tedious. The character development was there although in some cases there was probably more than we needed. If you are looking for a traditional horror story, you'll probably be disappointed. If you enjoy horror, spy tales, and superhero stories, then you should like this one. Overall, I think this is one you just have to decide on for yourself. There are several books in the series, and I can't say whether I will read them all. I will however, read at least the next few to see where the story goes.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4095275692768391766" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

