  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1411247533" />
    <a title="Ctgt" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3787451-ctgt"><img alt="Ctgt" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1524569344p2/3787451.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1411247533?book_show_action=true">Oct 07, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ctgt" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ctgt" href="/user/show/3787451-ctgt">Ctgt</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780812521375" href="/book/show/1063376.Necroscope">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3787451-ctgt?shelf=horror">horror</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1411247533" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7265302780901427858">I really should have loved this book, set in the years after WII with the traditional Cold War adversaries and an added supernatural twist, competing divisions made up of agents with unusual abilities. But there were long passages of background information that I really struggled to wade through. This is a series of books so I guess you can consider this a set-up book but it just seemed like there could have been a better way to incorporate all the information without resorting to these extended</span>
  <span id="freeText7265302780901427858" style="display:none">I really should have loved this book, set in the years after WII with the traditional Cold War adversaries and an added supernatural twist, competing divisions made up of agents with unusual abilities. But there were long passages of background information that I really struggled to wade through. This is a series of books so I guess you can consider this a set-up book but it just seemed like there could have been a better way to incorporate all the information without resorting to these extended segments of info dumps. There are some great scenes, including a fantastically horrific autopsy that I won't soon forget and the powers some the agents possess offer great possibilities. So even with my unhappiness with parts of the book I will still check out the next book in the series. <br /><br />6/10</span>
  <a data-text-id="7265302780901427858" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


